(240, 2, '2014-07-12 15:14:55', '2014-07-12 15:14:55', '[et_pb_section background_color="#ed1c24" inner_shadow="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="css"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image" src="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ddlogo.png" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" animation="left" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="2_3"][et_pb_cta admin_label="Call To Action" title="What is Domocracy?" use_background_color="on" background_color="#dd3333" background_layout="dark" text_orientation="center"]<p>Today, everybody should have access to Smart Homes technology. However, existing solutions in the market are too expensive and too complex for most people to even consider it.</p><p>As a consequence, the general public has a vision that Domotics are expensive and hard to use. That’s why we have developed a technology that allows us to manufacture smart devices at the price of normal ones. We don’t expect people to buy our products because they are intelligent, but because for the same price they get extra value. This way, by the time you realise, your home will already be smart.</p><p>Why Domocracy? Domocracy is a technology affordable for anyone. It is cheap and easy to use. Based on concepts like “plug &amp; play” and on mobile technologies, Domocracy brings smart technology to homes all over the world like no one before.</p>[/et_pb_cta][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Faq', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '239-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-12 15:14:55', '2014-07-12 15:14:55', '', 239, 'http://localhost/239-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
