(469, 6, '2014-12-29 12:34:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'After development reaches a certain point, a time comes where you need to scale things up.\r\n\r\nThis is where we are now, and the reason why we need your help. Our prototype is functional, our key technologies are validated, and we are ready for the next step.\r\n\r\nThis step comes down to three different tasks: Polishing, Certification and Production.\r\n\r\nPolishing is the process of taking the prototype from the development phase to the market ready stage. We want to integrate the community deeply in this process in order to get the best out of it. During this polishing phase we are releasing early SDKs that will allow developers to take a first look at our APIs and help us get the simplest and most efficient interface for everyone to play with our technology. This early feedback will probably lead to great improvements in both user experience and the core technology supporting it. After we integrate these changes, we will consider Domocracy is ready for the first run.\r\n\r\nThere begins the certification process. Certification ensures that our base technology, as well as all devices we build on top of that, is fully compliant with regulations in the USA and other countries we support. It is an important process for us and our customers, because it guarantees safety and interoperability within a home environment.\r\n\r\nCertification must be independently completed for every device type (lightbulbs, plugs, switches…) and is different for different countries, so it will consume a big part of our resources.\r\n\r\nAnd finally the best part: Production. This is where we get the big machinery running. Heat up the engine, unfold wings, begin the countdown, and launch! Once the prototype is market ready, validated and certified, we can prepare our plastic injection moulds, start baking pcbs and produce the first batch of devices. Most of the money will be spent here. We are adjusting manufacturing costs to the very minimum, but still, manufacturing, assembly and packaging of all devices account for most of our kickStarter goal.\r\n\r\nOf course there are risks ahead of us. We have accounted for various iterations to our products due to feedback coming from developers. However, changes in the development schedule or problems during the certification process can affect the final release dates. We are eager to start polishing, developing and interacting with the community, and ready to face any challenges ahead. With your help, and all the hard work of our team, we will deliver a great product to the world.\r\n\r\nWe are at the beginning of an amazing journey. We are living this adventure with a lot of illusion and with all our commitment, and hope you can join us all along. Help us, and be part of the change.', 'Why we need your help', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2014-12-29 12:34:01', '2014-12-29 12:34:01', '', 0, 'http://www.domocracytech.com/?p=469', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(470, 6, '2014-12-29 12:33:53', '2014-12-29 12:33:53', 'After development reaches a certain point, a time comes where you need to scale things up.\r\n\r\nThis is where we are now, and the reason why we need your help. Our prototype is functional, our key technologies are validated, and we are ready for the next step.\r\n\r\nThis step comes down to three different tasks: Polishing, Certification and Production.\r\n\r\nPolishing is the process of taking the prototype from the development phase to the market ready stage. We want to integrate the community deeply in this process in order to get the best out of it. During this polishing phase we are releasing early SDKs that will allow developers to take a first look at our APIs and help us get the simplest and most efficient interface for everyone to play with our technology. This early feedback will probably lead to great improvements in both user experience and the core technology supporting it. After we integrate these changes, we will consider Domocracy is ready for the first run.\r\n\r\nThere begins the certification process. Certification ensures that our base technology, as well as all devices we build on top of that, is fully compliant with regulations in the USA and other countries we support. It is an important process for us and our customers, because it guarantees safety and interoperability within a home environment.\r\n\r\nCertification must be independently completed for every device type (lightbulbs, plugs, switches…) and is different for different countries, so it will consume a big part of our resources.\r\n\r\nAnd finally the best part: Production. This is where we get the big machinery running. Heat up the engine, unfold wings, begin the countdown, and launch! Once the prototype is market ready, validated and certified, we can prepare our plastic injection moulds, start baking pcbs and produce the first batch of devices. Most of the money will be spent here. We are adjusting manufacturing costs to the very minimum, but still, manufacturing, assembly and packaging of all devices account for most of our kickStarter goal.\r\n\r\nOf course there are risks ahead of us. We have accounted for various iterations to our products due to feedback coming from developers. However, changes in the development schedule or problems during the certification process can affect the final release dates. We are eager to start polishing, developing and interacting with the community, and ready to face any challenges ahead. With your help, and all the hard work of our team, we will deliver a great product to the world.\r\n\r\nWe are at the beginning of an amazing journey. We are living this adventure with a lot of illusion and with all our commitment, and hope you can join us all along. Help us, and be part of the change.', 'Why we need your help', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '469-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-29 12:33:53', '2014-12-29 12:33:53', '', 469, 'http://www.domocracytech.com/469-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
