(473, 2, '2014-12-30 12:40:09', '2014-12-30 12:40:09', 'When we talk about automating a dwelling, we always think of elements such as television, illumination and air conditioning. To summarize somehow, <strong> all those things that involve energy management, security, communication, and ultimately, home well being</strong>. However, a subject so technological as videogames seems to stay out of the equation a priori.\n\nGiven the features of the latest technologies applied to electronic entertainment regarding remote control, an automated environment seems clearly suitable to manage and exploit these capabilities. One of the most interesting examples can be found in the new generation of game consoles, with Xbox One and Play Station 4 as the the top representatives.\n\nIn the case of the latter, it is worth mentioning the very interesting service “<strong>Share play</strong>”, which will allow users to access their video games remotely without the need to have their account activated and, most importantly, without needing to physically have the game with him. In the same way, PS4 holds the remarcable option of sharing your saved game across devices, allowing you to play in the handheld Ps Vita or specific mobile platforms to your home game console titles.\n\nTaking into account the open potential offered by domocracy regarding domotics, plenty of new options come into play that allow us to make the most out of “share play” without even needing to be in front of the hardware to handle it. Being video games a field that we can find in nearly every home, it would be irresponsible on our side to ignore it for what it can add to the concept of “smart home”. And of ourse, the options presented by new technologies show promeses of integrating more than ever in the sofisticated environment of tailored smart home. In that sense, we can start to say loud and clear that <b>Video games need Domocracy.</b>', 'Video Games need Domocracy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '457-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-12-30 12:40:09', '2014-12-30 12:40:09', '', 457, 'http://www.domocracytech.com/457-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
